2.4

Intercept means that country with 0 GDP per capita ($) would have a mean of 6.864e+01 (years) Life expectancy at birth The GDP_PC means that as GDP per capita increase 1 unit, the life expectancy would increase by 2.477e-04 (years) The relationship between GDP and life expectancy statistically significant, since p value is less than 0.5
